 utter decent language. ','qrus' => ' Грязный рот не скажет достойных слов. ','auth' => ' <span title= ><b>Chinese Proverb</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://wf360.typepad.com/bev/2007/02/index.html">wf360.typepad.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '29','eng' => 'indecent','trans' => 'ɪnˈdiːsənt','rus' => 'недостойный, непорядочный','qeng' => ' I don&rsquo;t see how an article of clothing can be indecent. A person, yes. ','qrus' => ' Я не понимаю, как предмет одежды может быть недостойным. Человек - да. ','auth' => ' <span title=(1907-1988),&nbsp;American&nbsp;science&nbsp;fiction&nbsp;writer><b>Robert Heinlein</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/italy/2977111/Rome-mayor-cracks-down-on-skimpy-clothing-distracting-motorists.html">telegraph.co.uk</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '29','eng' => 'virtue','trans' => 'ˈvɜːtjuː','rus' => 'добродетель, достоинство','qeng' => ' He has all of the virtues I dislike and none of the vices I admire. ','qrus' => ' У него есть все те достоинства, которые я не люблю, и ни одного недостатка из тех, что мне нравятся. ','auth' => ' <span title=(1874&nbsp;-&nbsp;1965),&nbsp;British&nbsp;politician&nbsp;and&nbsp;statesman><b>Winston Churchill</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.tubecad.com/2009/12/blog0178.htm">tubecad.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '29','eng' => 'wicked','trans' => 'ˈwɪkɪd','rus' => 'злой, грешный, свирепый, опасный','qeng' => ' Wicked cows have short horns. ','qrus' => ' У злобных коров короткие рога. ','auth' => ' <span title= ><b>Dutch proverb</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/62333110@N02/6612834601/">flickr.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '29','eng' => 'vicious','trans' => 'ˈvɪʃəs','rus' => 'злобный, порочный, ужасный','qeng' => ' As we ascend the social ladder, viciousness wears a thicker mask. ','qrus' => ' При поднятии по социальной лестнице маск порока становится толще. ','auth' => ' <span title=(1900-1980),&nbsp;German&nbsp;born&nbsp;American&nbsp;social&nbsp;philosopher&nbsp;and&nbsp;psychoanalyst><b>Erich Fromm</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://blog.samerbsaleh.com/?p=364">blog.samerbsaleh.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '29','eng' => 'brute','trans' => 'bruːt','rus' => 'грубый, животный','qeng' => ' I can stand brute force but brute reason is quite unbearable. ','qrus' => ' Я могу вынести грубую силу, но грубый разум невывосим. ','auth' => ' <span title=(1854-1900),&nbsp;Irish&nbsp;poet,&nbsp;novelist,&nbsp;dramatist&nbsp;and&nbsp;critic><b>Oscar Wilde</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://sketchflood.blogspot.com/2006/12/wolverbear.html">sketchflood.blogspot.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '29','eng' => 'dignity','trans' => 'ˈdɪgnɪtɪ','rus' => 'благородство или достоинство','qeng' => ' Dignity and love do not blend well, nor do they continue long together. ','qrus' => ' Благородство и любовь не сочетаются и не держатся долго вместе. ','auth' => ' <span title=(43&nbsp;BC&nbsp;-&nbsp;17&nbsp;AD),&nbsp;Ancient&nbsp;Roman&nbsp;classical&nbsp;poet><b>Ovid</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.wisegeek.org/in-chemistry-what-is-a-heterogeneous-mixture.htm">wisegeek.org</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '29','eng' => 'conscience','trans' => 'ˈkɒnʃəns','rus' => 'совесть','qeng' => ' Conscience reigns but it does not govern. ','qrus' => ' Совесть царит, но не управляет. ','auth' => ' <span title=(1871-1945),&nbsp;French&nbsp;poet,&nbsp;essayist,&nbsp;and&nbsp;philosopher><b>Paul Valery</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://rolynjane54.blogspot.com/2011/09/conscience-stricken.html">rolynjane54.blogspot.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '29','eng' => 'nobility','trans' => 'nəʊˈbɪlɪtɪ','rus' => 'благородство','qeng' => ' There is nothing noble in being superior to somebody else. The only real nobility is in being superior to your former self. ','qrus' => ' Нет ничего благородного в том, чтобы быть вы