ument?docid=4182">nova-docdb.fnal.gov</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'circle','trans' => 'ˈsɜːkl','rus' => 'круг или окружность','qeng' => ' God is a circle whose center is everywhere and circumference nowhere. ','qrus' => ' Бог - это круг, чей центр находится везде, а окружность - нигде. ','auth' => ' <span title=(1694-1778),&nbsp;French&nbsp;Enlightenment&nbsp;writer,&nbsp;historian&nbsp;and&nbsp;philosopher><b>Francois Voltaire</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.mathopenref.com/constinpentagon.html">mathopenref.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'point','trans' => 'ˈpɔɪnt','rus' => 'кончик','qeng' => ' When you shoot an arrow of truth, dip its point in honey. ','qrus' => ' Пуская стрелу правды, окуни её кончик в мёд. ','auth' => ' <span title= ><b>Arabian proverb</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://eaarcherysolutions.com/">eaarcherysolutions.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'tip','trans' => 'tɪp','rus' => 'кончик','qeng' => ' I pointed out to you the moon and all you saw was the tip of my finger. ','qrus' => ' Я указал тебе на луну, но ты увидел только кончик моего пальца. ','auth' => ' <span title= ><b>Chinese Proverb</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://spermsandomelette.wordpress.com/2011/08/26/finger-pointing-to-the-moon/">spermsandomelette.wordpress.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'point','trans' => 'ˈpɔɪnt','rus' => 'точка','qeng' => ' From an identity standpoint, what does it mean to have a disability? Pamela Anderson has more prosthetic in her body than I do and nobody calls her disabled. ','qrus' => ' С точки зрения личности, что означает инвалидность? В теле Памелы Андерсон больше протезного материала, чем у меня, и никто не называет её инвалидом. ','auth' => ' <span title=(b&nbsp;1976),&nbsp;American&nbsp;athlete,&nbsp;actress,&nbsp;and&nbsp;fashion&nbsp;model&nbsp;best&nbsp;known&nbsp;for&nbsp;her&nbsp;collegiate-level&nbsp;athletic&nbsp;accomplishments,&nbsp;despite&nbsp;a&nbsp;medical&nbsp;condition&nbsp;that&nbsp;resulted&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;amputation&nbsp;of&nbsp;both&nbsp;of&nbsp;her&nbsp;legs.,&nbsp;&amp;How&nbsp;My&nbsp;Legs&nbsp;Give&nbsp;Me&nbsp;Super-Powers&amp; ><b>Aimee Mullins</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.myhero.com/go/hero.asp?hero=Aimee_Mullins">myhero.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'rim','trans' => 'rɪm','rus' => 'ободок, край','qeng' => ' What is laid down, ordered, factual is never enough to embrace the whole truth: life always spills over the rim of every cup. ','qrus' => ' Что разложено в порядке, по фактам, никогда не объемлет всю правду, жизнь всегда перельётся через край любой чашки. ','auth' => ' <span title=(1890&nbsp;-&nbsp;1960),&nbsp;Russian&nbsp;author><b>Boris Pasternak</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.document-shredding-services-nj-media-storage-pa-de.com/storage.php">document-shredding-services-nj-media-storage-pa-de.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'square','trans' => 'skwɛə','rus' => 'квадрат/квадратный','qeng' => ' Life is a chessboard with one piece and one square. ','qrus' => ' Жизнь - это шахматная доска с одной фигурой и одной клеткой. ','auth' => ' <span title=(b.&nbsp;1967),&nbsp;English&nbsp;author&nbsp;of&nbsp;satirical&nbsp;science&nbsp;fiction&nbsp;and&nbsp;several&nbsp;bizarro&nbsp;books><b>Steve Aylett</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2008/05/26/bloggers-are-like-pawns-on-a-chessboard/">problogger.net</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'layer','trans' => 'ˈleɪə','rus' => 'слой','qeng' => ' Life is like an onion: you peel it off one layer at a time, and sometimes you weep. ','qrus' => ' Жизнь как лук - за раз счищаешь один слой и иногда плачешь. ','auth' => ' <span title=(1878-1967),&nbsp;American&nbsp;writer&nbsp;and&nbsp;editor><b>Carl Sandburg</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://todefyego.blogspot.com/2011/10/peeling-back-another-layer.html">todefyego.blogspot.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'straight','trans' => 'streɪt','rus' => 'прямой/прямо','qeng' => ' You cannot drive straight on a twisting lane. ','qrus' => ' По кривой улочке прямо не поедешь. ','auth' => ' <span title= ><b>Russian Proverb</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.homeaway.com/vacation-rental/p167524">homeaway.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'internal','trans' => 'ɪnˈtɜːnəl','rus' => 'внутренний','qeng' => ' The face is not a secondary billboard for our internal feelings. It is an equal partner in the emotional process. ','qrus' => ' Лицо - вовсе не вторично, это не афиша наших внутренних чувств. Это равный участник эмоционального процесса. ','auth' => ' <span title=(b.&nbsp;1963),&nbsp;Canadian&nbsp;journalist,&nbsp;bestselling&nbsp;author,&nbsp;and&nbsp;speaker,&nbsp;&amp;Blink:&nbsp;The&nbsp;Power&nbsp;of&nbsp;Thinking&nbsp;Without&nbsp;Thinking,&nbsp;2005&amp; ><b>Malcolm Gladwell</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2009/08/090813142131.htm">sciencedaily.com</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'external','trans' => 'ɪkˈstɜːnəl','rus' => 'наружный, внешний','qeng' => ' He that would be superior to external influences must first become superior to his own passions. ','qrus' => ' Кто хочет быть сильнее внешних обстоятельств, должен сначала подняться над своими страстями. ','auth' => ' <span title=(1709-1784),&nbsp;English&nbsp;poet,&nbsp;critic&nbsp;and&nbsp;writer><b>Samuel Johnson</b></span><br>Photo:<br><a href="http://www.themillionairesecrets.net/12-keys-to-success-control-your-emotion/">themillionairesecrets.net</a> ','state' => '1'],['category_id' => '62','eng' => 'outward','trans' => 'ˈaʊtwəd','rus' => 'внешний, наружний','qeng' => ' Too many of our prejudices are like pyramids upside down. They rest on tiny, trivial incidents, but they spread upward and outward until they fill our minds. ',